@startuml
title Cache Deployment - Current and Target Backend Swap

skinparam linetype ortho

node "CLI / Commands" as CLI {
  component "enrich/match/resolve/\ncache refresh/apply" as Commands
}

node "Application Runtime" as APP {
  component "UseCases + Stages" as Stages
  component "Role-based cache ports\n(EnrichLookupPort, MatchRuntimePort,\nResolveRuntimePort, ApplyRuntimePort, CacheAdminPort)" as Ports
  component "cache_gateway object\n(SqliteCacheGateway)" as Gateway
}

node "Current Infra" as CUR {
  database "SQLite" as SqliteDB
  component "SqliteCacheRepository" as SqliteCacheRepo
  component "SqliteIdentityRepository" as SqliteIdentityRepo
  component "SqlitePendingLinksRepository" as SqlitePendingRepo
}

node "Target Infra (future)" as FUT {
  database "Redis / alternative store" as RedisDB
  component "RedisCacheGateway\n(planned)" as RedisGateway
}

CLI --> Commands
Commands --> Stages
Stages ..> Ports
Ports <.. Gateway
Gateway *--> SqliteCacheRepo
Gateway *--> SqliteIdentityRepo
Gateway *--> SqlitePendingRepo

SqliteCacheRepo --> SqliteDB
SqliteIdentityRepo --> SqliteDB
SqlitePendingRepo --> SqliteDB

RedisGateway --> RedisDB
Ports <.. RedisGateway : same role contracts

note bottom of APP
Backend swap should not affect
stage/use-case contracts while
role ports remain stable.
end note

@enduml

